380
00:16:18.890 --> 00:16:22.090
Wow! This place is great!

381
00:16:22.880 --> 00:16:26.490
Lovely Street is Angel Island's
only shopping center.

382
00:16:28.430 --> 00:16:31.010
Check it out! The stores are floating!

383
00:16:31.630 --> 00:16:35.160
They're built using the special
properties of island clouds.

384
00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:38.020
Wow! Any barbecue shops?

385
00:16:49.370 --> 00:16:52.890
Is it just me, or is
everyone avoiding us?

386
00:16:52.890 --> 00:16:54.180
Can't blame 'em.

387
00:16:54.180 --> 00:16:58.000
Word's probably gotten
out that we're criminals.

388
00:17:00.360 --> 00:17:01.690
This feels great!

389
00:17:01.690 --> 00:17:03.590
We've got the whole
place to ourselves!

390
00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:07.210
All the angels are avoiding me...

391
00:17:09.610 --> 00:17:12.930
Oh? There sure is
a lot of weird stuff for sale!

392
00:17:15.500 --> 00:17:20.070
This one's nice! Too bad I'm broke.
Is a treasure payment plan okay?

393
00:17:20.070 --> 00:17:20.970
No, no!

394
00:17:21.650 --> 00:17:25.220
Luffy! This isn't the time
to be fooling around!

395
00:17:25.220 --> 00:17:27.390
Nami's group will be sacrificed!

396
00:17:27.390 --> 00:17:29.600
Do you even want to save them?!

397
00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:33.700
Save them? They're gonna be fine!
Zoro was caught with them!

398
00:17:33.700 --> 00:17:35.840
Like we can really count on him!

399
00:17:35.840 --> 00:17:40.660
With how crazy things have been,
I hope the ship is still in one piece.

400
00:17:40.980 --> 00:17:43.350
Huh?! There's something in the street!

401
00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:43.980
Huh?

402
00:17:50.220 --> 00:17:53.260
What a weird face!
What is this? A seal?

403
00:17:53.260 --> 00:17:57.660
Some kind of weird mud figure,
so maybe it's a religious statue?

404
00:17:57.660 --> 00:18:00.950
Morons! This is art! I can tell!

405
00:18:00.950 --> 00:18:02.440
It's "vearth."

406
00:18:02.940 --> 00:18:07.150
The people of the sky
have always admired it.

407
00:18:07.150 --> 00:18:08.440
"Vearth"?

408
00:18:08.440 --> 00:18:14.030
What? You guys admire this thing?
You must be crazy...

409
00:18:16.220 --> 00:18:21.160
Yes, I'm sure it must be difficult
for Blue Sea people to understand.

410
00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:23.340
Oh, the docks are this way!

411
00:18:23.340 --> 00:18:25.440
What? We're leaving town already?!

412
00:18:25.440 --> 00:18:28.900
What are you talking about?!
We have somewhere to be!

413
00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:31.730
Would it hurt to hang
around a little longer?

414
00:18:59.280 --> 00:19:00.740
– Whoa!
– Whoa!

415
00:19:00.740 --> 00:19:02.750
So many boats!

416
00:19:04.140 --> 00:19:07.250
There are all kinds of
boats anchored here.

417
00:19:12.090 --> 00:19:15.380
Whoa! Check out this gondola!

418
00:19:18.030 --> 00:19:21.100
It's so cool! Let's borrow it!

419
00:19:21.720 --> 00:19:26.000
Look behind it! This one can
move on its own, like a waver!

420
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:28.910
I smell a fun gondola adventure!

421
00:19:28.910 --> 00:19:33.660
We're rescuing Nami and Robin,
you idiot! Get serious!

422
00:19:33.660 --> 00:19:36.270
Oh, your boat is over here.

423
00:19:36.270 --> 00:19:36.780
Right!

424
00:19:36.780 --> 00:19:38.030
– Oh?!
– Oh?!

425
00:19:39.030 --> 00:19:42.290
Oh, boy! What kind of gondola is it?!

426
00:19:53.420 --> 00:19:54.720
The Little Crow!

427
00:19:57.550 --> 00:19:59.260
You can't be serious!

428
00:19:59.260 --> 00:20:00.450
Crows...

429
00:20:01.720 --> 00:20:03.350
aren't even waterfowl.

430
00:20:04.540 --> 00:20:08.650
I used it until recently,
when I learned how to ride wavers.

431
00:20:09.200 --> 00:20:14.110
It's not as fast as a waver,
but it does run on two breath dials.

432
00:20:14.610 --> 00:20:16.320
Please feel free to use it!

433
00:20:17.790 --> 00:20:19.530
No... I'm not going.

434
00:20:20.620 --> 00:20:22.030
Just as I expected!

435
00:20:22.030 --> 00:20:24.330
He shows his true colors
at the last minute!

436
00:20:24.330 --> 00:20:26.410
I wanna use that one instead.

437
00:20:30.860 --> 00:20:32.840
It was just about the ship?

438
00:20:34.590 --> 00:20:38.380
Y-You don't like it? I'm sorry. But...

439
00:20:38.380 --> 00:20:41.100
You damn ingrate! Apologize!

440
00:20:41.100 --> 00:20:44.780
Apologize to Conis from the bottom
of your heart, you scumbag!

441
00:20:44.780 --> 00:20:47.690
Pay no attention to his selfishness!

442
00:20:47.690 --> 00:20:49.070
Sorry!

443
00:20:49.070 --> 00:20:49.600
Yes...

444
00:20:49.600 --> 00:20:52.020
Your exit is gate number two.

445
00:20:52.890 --> 00:20:57.170
It will lead you to a giant milky road,
which connects to Upper Yard.

446
00:20:58.030 --> 00:21:01.120
Th-The route is as simple as that.

447
00:21:04.000 --> 00:21:05.870
Hey, Conis.

448
00:21:06.400 --> 00:21:07.000
Yes?

449
00:21:07.360 --> 00:21:10.750
Why have you been shaking
ever since we left your house?

450
00:21:14.380 --> 00:21:17.880
Wh-What the hell is he saying?!

451
00:21:19.280 --> 00:21:20.990
D-Does it seem that way?

452
00:21:23.550 --> 00:21:26.560
Yeah. It's like you're
afraid of something...

453
00:21:28.520 --> 00:21:30.930
No! Is she...?

454
00:21:33.390 --> 00:21:38.940
Conis! You're worried
about us! That's so touching!

455
00:21:40.900 --> 00:21:44.910
Still, are you and your father
gonna be okay?!

456
00:21:44.910 --> 00:21:48.760
Everyone in town is
obviously avoiding us,

457
00:21:48.760 --> 00:21:53.710
yet you're lending us your boat
and even giving us directions...

458
00:21:54.460 --> 00:21:57.840
Doesn't that make you
our accomplices?

459
00:21:58.500 --> 00:22:01.340
You're looking real pale, too...

460
00:22:03.670 --> 00:22:06.290
You should've told us
if you were that scared.

461
00:22:06.290 --> 00:22:08.270
We would've come here on our own...

462
00:22:08.270 --> 00:22:09.190
No.

463
00:22:10.230 --> 00:22:11.370
I'm...

464
00:22:11.920 --> 00:22:13.170
It's not what you think!

465
00:22:17.280 --> 00:22:18.820
She wouldn't!

466
00:22:19.620 --> 00:22:21.820
Don't say anything you shouldn't!

467
00:22:22.880 --> 00:22:24.780
It is strange, isn't it?

468
00:22:25.320 --> 00:22:30.700
Explaining the route to your ordeal,
guiding you here myself...

469
00:22:30.700 --> 00:22:35.670
It's like I want to lead you there,
despite saying how terrifying it is...

470
00:22:37.630 --> 00:22:41.510
Stop it! Don't say
something you'll regret!

471
00:22:41.510 --> 00:22:43.880
Huh? What was that?

472
00:22:54.020 --> 00:22:56.860
Don't tell me they're all...

473
00:23:02.390 --> 00:23:08.070
It is our citizens' duty. It is his will.

474
00:23:15.080 --> 00:23:16.730
Could you run away?

475
00:23:22.510 --> 00:23:24.080
I'm so sorry!

476
00:23:27.720 --> 00:23:29.100
Stop!

477
00:23:29.100 --> 00:23:30.680
What are you saying?!

478
00:23:31.420 --> 00:23:35.630
I was the one who called
the superexpress lobster!

479
00:23:36.540 --> 00:23:39.340
The thing that took Nami
and the others?!

480
00:23:39.340 --> 00:23:40.520
You called it?!

481
00:23:43.050 --> 00:23:47.640
While you were back at the house,

482
00:23:47.640 --> 00:23:51.070
I lied to them about a current
that leads to Cloud End

483
00:23:51.640 --> 00:23:53.530
and had them raise the anchor.

484
00:23:59.000 --> 00:24:02.990
That was the signal
for the superexpress lobster.

485
00:24:12.850 --> 00:24:14.560
Foolish girl! Do you want to die?!

486
00:24:14.560 --> 00:24:16.560
This is our duty!

487
00:24:16.560 --> 00:24:18.140
Once we know someone's a criminal,

488
00:24:18.140 --> 00:24:23.480
we'll be killed if we don't lead them
to the place of reckoning!

489
00:24:25.440 --> 00:24:29.080
Stop it! Do you realize
what you're saying?!

490
00:24:29.080 --> 00:24:30.510
That's blasphemy!

491
00:24:30.510 --> 00:24:32.370
Stop her!

492
00:24:32.370 --> 00:24:35.370
This is our duty as citizens.

493
00:24:35.370 --> 00:24:37.130
Are you serious?!

494
00:24:37.130 --> 00:24:38.410
I'm sorry!

495
00:24:39.180 --> 00:24:42.160
It's all so strange, isn't it?!

496
00:24:43.750 --> 00:24:48.130
Don't be stupid! You didn't
have any choice, right?!

497
00:24:51.560 --> 00:24:52.550
So then...

498
00:24:56.000 --> 00:24:57.850
– ...why are you telling us?!
– ...why are you telling us?!

499
00:25:02.400 --> 00:25:04.630
Your life is in danger!

500
00:25:04.630 --> 00:25:06.170
It's all over!

501
00:25:06.170 --> 00:25:07.530
We're too late!

502
00:25:07.530 --> 00:25:08.980
Stay away from the girl!

503
00:25:08.980 --> 00:25:10.490
Reckoning is coming!

504
00:25:47.720 --> 00:25:48.990
No good! It's too big!

505
00:26:33.290 --> 00:26:34.950
What was that?!

506
00:26:35.480 --> 00:26:36.990
What just happened?!

507
00:26:38.420 --> 00:26:39.360
Luffy!

508
00:26:39.360 --> 00:26:42.270
Conis! Hey! Where'd you go?!

509
00:26:42.910 --> 00:26:45.420
Luffy! Conis!

510
00:26:45.840 --> 00:26:47.040
It's no use...

511
00:26:47.040 --> 00:26:50.340
The almighty God Enel sees all...!

512
00:26:54.130 --> 00:26:56.430
They are both safe.

513
00:27:02.590 --> 00:27:04.250
It's Gan Fall!

514
00:27:06.540 --> 00:27:08.400
Hey, it's that old weirdo!

515
00:27:08.700 --> 00:27:10.080
"Weirdo"?

516
00:27:10.080 --> 00:27:14.700
No, I am the Sky Knight!
This one is on the house!

517
00:27:18.460 --> 00:27:20.910
Thank goodness! Conis...!

518
00:27:21.840 --> 00:27:27.380
Leave this girl with me.
I will not allow Enel to harm her.

519
00:27:28.460 --> 00:27:29.460
Good!

520
00:27:29.460 --> 00:27:34.750
You now know this land's true nature,
as well as God's power.

521
00:27:34.750 --> 00:27:37.050
What will you do now?

522
00:27:37.050 --> 00:27:39.490
I don't care what
happens to this place.

523
00:27:40.680 --> 00:27:42.930
Our friends are on God's Island.

524
00:27:43.440 --> 00:27:46.390
I see... May luck be with you.

525
00:27:56.440 --> 00:27:57.400
What about them?

526
00:27:57.400 --> 00:27:59.660
They have chosen their course.

527
00:27:59.660 --> 00:28:02.330
It is no fault of yours.

528
00:28:03.180 --> 00:28:06.210
I know who you are.

529
00:28:06.800 --> 00:28:09.530
I am the Sky Knight.

530
00:28:10.290 --> 00:28:15.300
No, we all know. Please come back...

531
00:28:15.870 --> 00:28:17.010
God!

532
00:28:22.270 --> 00:28:26.470
Get on! I'll give you
a strong push out!

533
00:28:26.470 --> 00:28:27.950
You're coming, too!

534
00:28:32.920 --> 00:28:35.400
Alright, let's go to Upper Yard!

535
00:28:38.730 --> 00:28:41.550
No...!

536
00:28:44.140 --> 00:28:45.900
The bastards actually left...

537
00:28:46.430 --> 00:28:49.290
with no hesitation
or uncertainty at all.
